 it is getting in a very big lead for the hotel, organizing large scale lifestyle events or setting up truly memorable experiences for in-house guests. Above all, Pamela is team focused and has developed numerous team members to strong performers.  ", "recommendations/1/name": "Pamela Ong Cheng Gaik", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "General Manager - Courtyard by Marriott Phuket Town at Marriott International", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/pamelaongcg/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAZrcrgBQGez2TlZOFMepfCBb5wc4dK33F4", "recommendations/2/context": "Nils managed Samiada directly", "recommendations/2/date": "April 18, 2015", "recommendations/2/description": "It has been an honor to have Samiada in my team during pre opening of The Stones, the first first Autograph Collection in AP. A very ambitious, smart and talented individual. Someone who has earned a first degree in how to energize his people and drive them for success. ", "recommendations/2/name": "Samiada Gede (Sam)", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Director Of Operations at Fairfield by Marriott Bali Legian", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/samiada-gede-sam-91932831/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAaiESUBi3I1wysMBPAe3wrftwgZLnWp6kM", "recommendations/3/context": "Nils reported directly to Lutz", "recommendations/3/date": "July 21, 2013", "recommendations/3/description": "Lutz has been been my direct report and mentor at Renaissance Koh Samui and I would highly recommend him to any five star international hotel. His people skills are exceptional and he has his ways to get his team on the way to get the job done. He also proved to be a role model in looking after our guests and I have learned a lot from him over the time we worked together.", "recommendations/3/name": "Lutz Mueller", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Executive Director & Co-Founder - German Kitchen Design", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/lutz-mueller-5645855/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD5eNwBg7juEH0Mr9ixSE677L1lL5u8hks", "recommendations/4/context": "Nils was senior to .Erik but didn't manage .Erik directly", "recommendations/4/date": "July 24, 2011", "recommendations/4/description": "Erik is a great guy to work with and in his function as manager of a renowned Italian restaurant in the prestigious Le Royal Meridien Shanghai he has been innovative with a great sense of market instinct and been very ambitious which inspired his team to be the best. I would recommend Erik in any hospitality related industry due to his flair, intelligence and eager to strive for results.", "recommendations/4/name": ".Erik Theeuwes", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Business Area Manager Albron Business Horeca", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/erik-theeuwes/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADyWqABGA6SNlBPyFHmGrGz8HBqsZY8vTQ", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "I Wayan worked with Nils on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "April 21, 2015", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "It has been privilege to have worked with Nils Minken for +2 years. Nils is a professional hotelier who knows inside and out of the field. He's a quick learner in adapting with new environment. His experiences in Business and Resort hotels have been enriching his skill and knowledge and know-how. He is a creative in finding ways of generating F&B Revenues. His leadership is an asset for him to take greater role and responsibility. ", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "I Wayan Ginastra", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Authentic, Cultural, Sanctuary", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/i-wayan-ginastra-88356030/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAZ9JuMBHv5E9GzhZGTfB_SR8418u1VFfMQ", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Andrew Paul was senior to Nils but didn't manage Nils directly", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "November 17, 2014", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "Nils is an impressive Lifestyle Leader. I have had the opportunity to this in different ways.... on-property where I have seen and experienced lifestyle under Nils' ledership and also via his participation in our Lifestyle University programs and platforms. I believe Nils truly gets the Lifestyle space and I get energised by what he does! ", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Andrew Paul Newmark", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Be inspired... Be empowered... Be you", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrew-paul-newmark-b40453b/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAIGD6ABq8gj9c80FWHd2vPWtkQAj0j9xwQ", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Lutz managed Nils directly", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "July 6, 2013", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "Nils is a very enthusiastic person who loves his job. He is creative, ambitious, focused and goal oriented. I have experienced Nils as a hands-on manager who leads his team by being a role model. He always strives for excellency, aims for innovation and stays up to date with industry trends.", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Lutz Mueller", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Executive Director & Co-Founder - German Kitchen Design", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/lutz-mueller-5645855/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAD5eNwBg7juEH0Mr9ixSE677L1lL5u8hks", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Adi was Nils's client", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "May 27, 2013", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "Nils has got that rare combination and series of academic training and experience that would produce a good decision maker  in the  unique global market of leisure of today..He got his first education in a prestigous hotel academy in Holland, then worked in China, Middle East and Bali. This thorough grounding,  add to his distinctly amiable  personality, would ease the way to strive to be a star performer. It has been a pleasure to work with him", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Adi Mudigdo", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "project manager at Cirta putra mandiri", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/adi-mudigdo-aa983557/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAwMKuEBfdJ5vsHC8wmndjrd3nUu4v7tuz0", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "Janet managed Nils directly", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "November 6, 2010", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "Friendly and fair leader, always open minded, honest\n\nWith hotel school back ground and wide  F&B experience in  China, including strategic plan ability, operation handling", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "Janet Si", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "General Manager", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/janet-si-a2673024/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAUXTL4Bm0Iz6QnMputeX4R5vifCMG856jI", "recommendationsReceived/5/context": "Tobias managed Nils directly", "recommendationsReceived/5/date": "March 17, 2009", "recommendationsReceived/5/description": "Nils is a very creative individual. He is outgoing and communicative and has a passion to build emotional connections with customers leading to high guest satisfaction. Nils is a highly motivated leader, who combines excellent product knowledge with very good strategic planning capability. A great guy to be with and to have fun.", "recommendationsReceived/5/name": "Tobias Ernst", "recommendationsReceived/5/subtitle": "Key Account Management", "recommendationsReceived/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/tobias-ernst/", "recommendationsReceived/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAE9EI4B5h5U0M2c-TMNnaO1gr7gW8lFFXI", "skills/0/title": "Hotel Management", "totalExperienceYears": "14", "totalRecommendationsGiven": "5", "totalRecommendationsReceived": "6", "updates/0/postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7308706228182888448?updateEntityUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afs_feedUpdate%3A%28V2%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7308706228182888448%29", "updates/0/postText": "🌿 Excited to Speak at the Sustainability for Business Forum 2025! 🌍\nI’m honored to be a speaker at the Sustainability for Business Forum 2025 (#SBF2025), where I’ll be sharing insights on waste management at Marriott—focusing on how we drive sustainability through innovative strategies that create business value while reducing environmental impact.\n\nA big thank you to the Franco-Thai Chamber of Commerce (FTCC), Netherlands-Thai Chamber of Commerce (NTCC), Swiss-Thai Chamber of Commerce (STCC), and Thai-Swedish Chamber of Commerce (SweCham) for organizing this impactful event. It’s inspiring to see businesses come together to advance sustainability and drive meaningful change.\n\nJoin us on May 29, 2025, at Bangkok Marriott Hotel The Surawongse, as we discuss cutting-edge waste management practices, sustainable cities, and leadership in sustainability. Looking forward to connecting with like-minded professionals who are passionate about making a difference!\n💡 Learn more: https://lnkd.in/g28rhYeQ\n\n#SBF2025 #Sustainability #WasteManagement #SustainableBusiness #CircularEconomy #Leadership #Marriott", "updates/0/type": "Post", "updates/1/postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7267067377320636416?updateEntityUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afs_feedUpdate%3A%28V2%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7267067377320636416%29", "updates/1/postText": "Unveiling the New Era of Yao Rooftop Bar: The Sky’s the Limit !\n\nSix months ago, we set out on an exciting journey to transform Yao Rooftop Bar at Marriott The Surawongse. Our goal was to redefine its image from a tourist spot with great views to a dynamic, lifestyle destination at the heart of Bangkok.\n\nWe began by redesigning the bar with a state-of-the-art counter and multiple bartender stations to enhance both creativity and efficiency. \n\nThe next step was bringing together the best talents in the city—leaders, mixologists, and guest engagement professionals—who helped craft extraordinary drinks and revamped menus with on-trend beverages. To top it off, we updated our team’s look with stylish new uniforms, further elevating the guest experience.\n\nPartnering with influential social media channels specializing in rooftop bars, we gained stunning visuals that beautifully showcase the transformation of Yao Rooftop Bar.\n\nTo keep the momentum going, we’ve planned an exciting series of events, featuring celebrity DJs, Asia’s 50 Best Bars bartenders, and collaborations with Bangkok’s hottest venues.\n\nDespite officially launching our new concept just a month ago, we’re already on track to reach record-breaking revenue for November—and we aim to surpass that milestone in December and beyond.\n\nThe moral of the story? Success starts with a detailed plan and, most importantly, recruiting the right talent. I’m incredibly proud of what we’ve accomplished and excited for what’s to come. \n\nWith Yao Rooftop Bar, the sky’s the limit!\n\n#YaoRooftopBar #HotelInnovation #HospitalityExcellence #BangkokNightlife #LeadershipInAction #BarInnovation #TalentDevelopment #TeamSuccess #RooftopBars Marriott International\nBangkok Marriott Hotel The Surawongse", "updates/1/type": "Post", "updates/2/postLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7252180658691743744?updateEntityUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afs_feedUpdate%3A%28V2%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7252180658691743744%29", "updates/2/postText": "I completed the MDA – Hotel Leadership Certificate, an 8-month program by Marriott International, designed to prepare future General Managers with essential leadership skills.\n\nMentored by Brad Edman, Market Vice President for Thailand, Cambodia, and Myanmar, I gained certification in 360 Leadership and 360 Finance, along with training in Loyalty, Finance, Marketing, and Integrity.\n\nA key development opportunity for me was representing my hotel at The Exchange roadshow in the Shanghai and Beijing markets, where I showcased our offerings and secured significant business opportunities.\n\nThank you to Marriott International for providing continuous opportunities for growth and development! \n\n#MarriottInternational #MarriottCareers #TalentDevelopment #Mentorship #BeMarriott Brad Edman", "updates/2/type": "Post", "urn": "ACoAAAJaV2EBIldwvcNQ3YvnRoCMqQrAXh53LiY"}$$::jsonb),
